          "body": "4:7-16 turns from the *one* to the *each*. The same Christ who unifies also distributes — *to each one of us grace was given according to the measure of Christ's gift* (4:7). Paul cites Psalm 68:18 (with a textual adaptation that has occupied commentators for centuries — Paul says *gave gifts* where the MT reads *received gifts*) to ground the church's offices in Christ's ascension triumph. The ascended Christ gives **gifted persons** — apostles, prophets, evangelists, pastor-teachers (4:11) — not to do ministry *for* the saints but *to equip* the saints to do the ministry themselves (4:12). The goal is corporate maturity (4:13), corporate stability against false doctrine (4:14), and corporate growth into the Head (4:15-16). The body is at once organism (it grows) and edifice (it is built up). Both images stand."
